      "comment": "KAKEGURUI (1) has mixed form recently, finishing sixth (17.63) in a Grade 4/5 at this track latest but did run well two back when in the frame. Key player on best and worth another chance. BLUE LACE (7) jumped from out wide and was game in defeat last start when a 0.8 lengths second (17.47) behind Tiny Twist at this track. Will give a great sight again. JUNK YARD LORAIN (2) collided with another runner and finished a well held 6 lengths fourth (17.54) last time in a Grade 6 at this track over 300m. Rates a key player and gets chance to atone. HARPER SMIRCH (8) is worth including after a top-three finish in a tight contest most recently.",
